						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīrachōḷadēva: Date lost: c. 12th—13th century.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged and incomplete and the date portion is lost. It appears to record another gift of land to the same deity as figures in No. 239 above, by the king on the request of the same person figuring therein, whose full name, however, was Araiśan Paṟaiyan <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śūttira[rāyaṉ] Poyyāttamiḻan.</p>						

